    "body": "Implements a generic rounding mode mechanism for Quack GEMM epilogues that\r\nconfigures how the accumulator (FP32) is downconverted to the output dtype\r\n(e.g., BF16) before storing to gmem. Stochastic rounding (RS) uses the\r\nhardware `cvt.rs.satfinite.bf16x2.f32` PTX instruction and is only supported\r\non SM100+ (Blackwell) GPUs.\r\n\r\n## Performance (BF16, GB200 @ 1020W, 20 warmup + 200 iters)\r\n\r\n| M | N | K | RN (us) | RS (us) | SR overhead | RN TFLOPS | RS TFLOPS |\r\n|---|---|---|---------|---------|-------------|-----------|-----------|\r\n| 1024 | 1024 | 1024 | 44.2 | 56.4 | +27.6% | 48.6 | 38.1 |\r\n| 2048 | 2048 | 2048 | 40.2 | 53.4 | +33.0% | 427.7 | 321.7 |\r\n| 4096 | 4096 | 4096 | 131.3 | 134.3 | +2.3% | 1047.0 | 1023.4 |\r\n| 8192 | 8192 | 8192 | 892.0 | 904.5 | +1.4% | 1232.7 | 1215.7 |\r\n| 16384 | 16384 | 16384 | 7182.4 | 7123.0 | -0.8% | 1224.7 | 1234.9 |\r\n| 16384 | 4096 | 4096 | 449.0 | 453.0 | +0.9% | 1224.3 | 1213.7 |\r\n| 16384 | 4096 | 8192 | 888.8 | 898.8 | +1.1% | 1237.0 | 1223.4 |\r\n| 16384 | 16384 | 4096 | 1776.2 | 1777.0 | +0.0% | 1238.0 | 1237.5 |\r\n| 4096 | 4096 | 16384 | 489.1 | 489.0 | -0.0% | 1124.0 | 1124.3 |\r\n| 8192 | 8192 | 4096 | 431.0 | 451.9 | +4.9% | 1275.6 | 1216.5 |\r\n| 16384 | 8192 | 1024 | 231.3 | 241.3 | +4.3% | 1188.2 | 1139.3 |\r\n\r\nSR overhead is <5% for compute-bound shapes (4K+ square and larger). Small\r\nshapes (1-2K square) show higher overhead since the epilogue is a larger\r\nfraction of total kernel time.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\nNew file: `quack/rounding.py`\r\n- `RoundingMode` enum (`IntEnum`): `RN` (round-to-nearest-even) and `RS` (stochastic)\r\n- `philox()`: Philox 4x32b CBRNG via inline PTX (7 rounds, standard constants)\r\n- `cvt_rs_f32x2_bf16x2()`: PTX `cvt.rs.satfinite.bf16x2.f32` wrapper\r\n- `convert_f32_to_bf16_sr()`: FP32 vector to BF16 with SR, pair-wise with Philox entropy\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/copy_utils.py`\r\n- Added `sr_cvt_copy()`: Like `cvt_copy` but uses stochastic rounding for FP32->BF16.\r\n  Takes `sr_seed` (dynamic `Int32`), `tidx` (thread index), `tile_seed` (per-tile seed).\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/gemm_default_epi.py`\r\n- `EpilogueArguments`: Added `rounding_mode` (`Constexpr`, compile-time cache key) and\r\n  `sr_seed` (`Optional[Int32]`, runtime dynamic — no recompilation on seed change)\r\n- `EpilogueParams`: Added `sr_seed`\r\n- `epi_to_underlying_arguments()`: Sets `self.rounding_mode` and passes `sr_seed`\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/gemm_sm90.py`\r\n- `epilogue()`: When `rounding_mode==RS`, computes tile seed from tile coordinates\r\n  (`m*65537 + n*257 + l*17 + subtile*7`) and calls `sr_cvt_copy` instead of `cvt_copy`\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/gemm_act.py`, `quack/gemm_dact.py`, `quack/gemm_symmetric.py`\r\n- Added `rounding_mode`/`sr_seed` fields to `EpilogueArguments` and `EpilogueParams`\r\n- Updated `epi_to_underlying_arguments()` to set `self.rounding_mode` and pass `sr_seed`\r\n- Updated epilogue `cvt_copy` calls with SR conditional (act and symmetric)\r\n- Updated call-time code to pass `None` for new `Constexpr`/runtime fields\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/gemm.py`\r\n- `_compile_gemm()`: Added `rounding_mode` to `@lru_cache` signature and cache key\r\n- `gemm()`: Added `rounding_mode` and `sr_seed` params. Asserts RS requires SM100+.\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/gemm_interface.py`\r\n- `gemm_tuned()`, `gemm()`, `gemm_out()`: Added `rounding_mode` and `sr_seed` params\r\n\r\nModified: `quack/__init__.py`\r\n- Exported `RoundingMode` for user access\r\n\r\nModified: `tests/test_linear.py`\r\n- `test_gemm_stochastic_rounding`: Validates SR results close to FP32 reference\r\n- `test_gemm_sr_requires_sm100`: Asserts RS raises on SM90\r\n- `test_gemm_sr_different_seeds`: Verifies different seeds produce different outputs\r\n",
